column4: Nowitzki turns back the clock  leads Mavs past new-look Lakers
column5: The 39-year-old Dirk Nowitzki turned back the clock by scoring a season-high 22 points on 8-of-11 shooting and Dallas made key plays down the stretch as the Mavericks defeated the new look Los Angeles Lakers 130-123 on Saturday at the American Airlines Center.

column4: Alibaba broadens offline reach with $865 million Easyhome stake
column5: BEIJING Alibaba Group Holding  will pay about 5.45 billion yuan ($866 million) for a 15 percent stake in China's Easyhome  a home improvement chain  as the internet giant expands its investments in offline and retail businesses.

column4: Citigroup to invest in London  hire staff despite Brexit: FT
column5: Wall Street bank Citigroup Inc  will set up an innovation center in London in one of the first investments by a big U.S. bank since Brexit  the Financial Times reported on Sunday.

column4: Credit Suisse hit by U.S. lawsuit over writedowns  says case "without merit"
column5: ZURICH Credit Suisse  faces a U.S. class action lawsuit over $1 billion in writedowns it took in 2015 and 2016 linked to its trading division  Swiss newspaper SonntagsZeitung reported on Sunday  but the Swiss bank said the case was "without merit".

column4: UPDATE 1-Takata  injured drivers reach deal to end U.S. bankruptcy
column5: WILMINGTON  Del.  Feb 11 Takata Corp's U.S. unit reached a settlement with its creditors  lawyers for those injured by its deadly air bags and automakers that smoothes the way to end its Chapter 11 bankruptcy and sell its viable operations  according to court papers.

column4: Disney raises prices of some U.S. theme park tickets
column5: NEW YORK Walt Disney Co said on Sunday it was changing the admission price for its U.S. theme parks  raising the cost of some single-day tickets by almost 9 percent.
